---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>dtolnay/serde-yaml</summary>

### [`v0.9.11`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.11)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.10...0.9.11)

-   Serialize strings on a single line when they do not already contain a newline character, regardless of string length ([#​321](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/321), [#​322](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/322))

### [`v0.9.10`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.10)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.9...0.9.10)

-   Make `Display` for `Number` produce the same representation as serializing ([#​316](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/316))

### [`v0.9.9`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.9)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.8...0.9.9)

-   Add [serde_yaml::with::singleton_map_recursive](https://docs.rs/serde_yaml/0.9.9/serde_yaml/with/singleton_map_recursive/index.html)

### [`v0.9.8`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.8)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.7...0.9.8)

-   Fix serialization of `TaggedValue` when used with `to_value` ([#​313](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/313))

### [`v0.9.7`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.7)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.6...0.9.7)

-   Allow an empty plain scalar to deserialize as an empty map or seq ([#​304](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/304))

### [`v0.9.6`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.6)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.5...0.9.6)

-   Fix tag not getting serialized in certain map values ([#​302](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/302))

### [`v0.9.5`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.5)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.4...0.9.5)

-   Implement `Display` trait for `serde_yaml::value::Tag` ([#​307](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/307), thanks [@​masinc](https://togithub.com/masinc))

### [`v0.9.4`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.4)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.3...0.9.4)

-   Add `serde_yaml::with::singleton_map` for serialization of enums as a 1-entry map ([#​300](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/300))
-   Reject duplicate keys when deserializing `Mapping` or `Value` ([#​301](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/issues/301))

### [`v0.9.3`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.2...0.9.3)

-   Add categories to crates.io metadata
-   Add keywords to crates.io metadata

### [`v0.9.2`](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/releases/tag/0.9.2)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/dtolnay/serde-yaml/compare/0.9.1...0.9.2)

-   Improve `Debug` representation of `serde_yaml::Error`

candidates.body:
[![Mend Renovate](https://app.renovatebot.com/images/banner.svg)](https://renovatebot.com)

This PR contains the following updates:

| Package | Type | Update | Change |

---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift</summary>

### [`v0.3.2`](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/releases/tag/0.3.2)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/compare/0.3.1...0.3.2)

#### What's Changed

-   Treat foo() { } as one call, not two by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/211](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/211)
-   Allow complex types in more places by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/212](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/212)
-   Allow pattern initializers without initialization expressions by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/212](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/212)
-   Differentiate between implicit and explicit semicolons by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/213](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/213)
-   Disallow `lazy` as a local variable modifier by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/214](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/214)
-   Allow a slash right before a string escape by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/215](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/215)
-   Allow actor to be used as an identifier by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/216](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/216)
-   Add support for very old Swift constructs by [@​alex-pinkus](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus) in [https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/217](https://togithub.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/pull/217)

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/alex-pinkus/tree-sitter-swift/compare/0.3.1...0.3.2

</details>
